Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.66,0:03:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As we expected, there's a fourth 5 tile inside
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.40,0:04:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, it's in there.\NThere's a 5 Sou (bamboo)!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last one...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okaay. Enough already
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.22,0:04:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a 5 Pin there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was also waiting on a 5 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That 5 Pin alone is enough. Case closed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,T-the FUCK?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.52,0:04:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the sole remaining tile
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.62,0:04:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,HUNH?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.22,0:04:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.96,0:05:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.19,0:05:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,His reading was flawless
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Harada himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.36,0:05:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to give it up half way through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.66,0:05:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That last tile
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.56,0:05:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it really {\b1\i1}ought{\b0\i0} to have been a 5 sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.14,0:05:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but in actuality it was 5 MAN
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada had ordered the 5 Sou and 5 Pin swapped with White Dragons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.42,0:05:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but his underling mistook the order, not using a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.82,0:05:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,instead swapping a 5 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.22,0:05:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A mistake like that, there's no way to predict it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but it doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.09,0:05:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was in fact waiting on a 5 Pin as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.86,0:05:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The win is confirmed. Harada said it himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.79,0:06:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter. Akagi's win is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.39,0:06:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada said it himself! Akagi has survived
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What Harada says has nothing to do with it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.66,0:06:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I declared a Ron on a 5 Sou\NAnd the missing tile wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.19,0:06:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, the result is all that matters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.76,0:06:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need it. Winning like that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.59,0:06:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've been here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.12,0:07:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Was fun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.89,0:07:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A most interesting man
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.61,0:07:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one is in Tenpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.51,0:07:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest isn't over yet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The day of the final will be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.11,0:07:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rules revised
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,both teams can suggest new ones
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.01,0:07:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.67,0:09:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For all of us, after all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world becomes of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'm a human being I will perish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and return to the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.44,0:09:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, after how many thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we're reborn as something else
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe as microbes spread throughout in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.91,0:09:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to be eaten by some faggy fish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.54,0:09:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe as some whelp,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or a bird
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really care when I die
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.24,0:09:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because life is reborn
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.11,0:10:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one thing that bothers me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.11,0:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when I, as a human being, drop dead
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.37,0:10:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is this feeling of {\b1\i1}who I am{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness will vanish
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What really scares me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.71,0:10:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is becoming what I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I win,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or should I fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.51,0:10:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\b1\i1}Akagi Shigeru{\b0\i0} who won...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or lost
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.24,0:10:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever Harada does is of no consquence
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided that tile was a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.17,0:10:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tile itself wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:10:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the sole thing that's important
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.81,0:11:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.24,0:11:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.34,0:11:34.81,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(647.245,579.124)}Day of the East/West Final
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.37,0:11:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had been you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.71,0:11:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,would you have done the same as Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.14,0:11:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I remain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.71,0:12:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't remain, you can't win
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.77,0:12:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Remain
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm me. You're you.\NAkagi is Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No one lives the same
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.21,0:12:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here and now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you and I have survived this far
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.91,0:12:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is everything
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.27,0:12:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.61,0:12:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I, above all else,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,concentrate wholeheartedly on victory
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and to that end I'll suggest a certain rule to the West team
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.71,0:12:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a rule which can best play to your logical nature
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.14,0:12:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ten, we've been waiting for you.\NThis way please
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.31,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Clear" Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Mahjong team variant that does without trading points
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.61,0:13:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rule which awards victory to the team who clears 5 agreed upon Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.54,0:13:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku one must clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.21,0:13:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are certain 2 Han Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.67,0:13:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ittsu, Sansyoku, Chanta, Chtoitsu, SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling tiles is allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.77,0:13:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you joking?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.21,0:13:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why we have to agree to a foolish game like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.51,0:13:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. We agree
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.94,0:13:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.94,0:13:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The normal point system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If a member goes bankrupt, that team loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.27,0:14:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not just pure luck
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.57,0:14:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're okay playing with both these rules together?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.54,0:14:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.41,0:14:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Proposing an idiotic rule like that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is proof enough they're cornered
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.21,0:15:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku which must be cleared...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.94,0:15:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,can largely be separated into two groups
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the first group, because it's a team game, offers protection against direct hits
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.47,0:16:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they are mobile, quick Yaku for which you can call tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.54,0:16:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,these are Ittsu, Sansyoku, and Chanta
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,there are laborious Yaku which you must construct on your own
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, Chitoitsu and SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.97,0:16:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically, of all five, SanAnKou is the biggest hurdle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say it has the number one level of difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.31,0:17:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.77,0:17:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A single suit hand？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:18:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The South team knows full well that SanAnKou is the key to Clear Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.72,0:18:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So If I declare a closed Kan,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.60,0:18:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the contrary, they ought to imagine I don't see the true worth a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga's going for a Chinisou?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.61,0:18:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I declare a 2nd closed Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.48,0:18:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as you'd expect, they'll perceive I'm aiming for a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.66,0:18:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.11,0:19:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!\NA confirmed SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.51,0:19:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only two 3 Sou tiles left
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.61,0:19:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a terrible wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but if Hiroyuki has a 3 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.61,0:19:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and deals it into my hand,\Nmy SanAnKou is complete
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.57,0:19:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki,\NDo you have any 3 Sou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.04,0:19:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What Sou tiles do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.41,0:19:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Sou, 7 Sou, 9 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, 1 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.47,0:19:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he deal into my hand at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.61,0:19:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as that's concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there's merely two tiles left on this 3/6 wait
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.71,0:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just waiting for a win is almost impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.94,0:20:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt he's got a Sou (Bamboo) single suit hand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.01,0:20:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can clearly see this from his two exposed calls
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.74,0:20:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a danger he's on a 4 or 5 Sou double sided wait
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the path I must take
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.94,0:20:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.11,0:20:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If I deal into his hand the risk of a foolish Haneman or Baiman hit is huge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.94,0:20:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.91,0:20:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Risk and Return are two sides of the same coin
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.91,0:20:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Into the jet black darkness of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.34,0:21:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to stick your hand into the terrifying deeps
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.61,0:21:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It... passed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.24,0:21:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, all Hiroyuki must do is deal in with his 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.71,0:21:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging merely by that Red Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.41,0:21:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he ought not be discarding dora which are likely to complete Soga's Chinisou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.07,0:21:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in tenpai for a huge hand
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.31,0:22:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A SanAnKou?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.51,0:22:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If I leave it be for one turn
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.27,0:22:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kid deals into it, it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.37,0:22:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.04,0:22:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.57,0:22:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.96,0:23:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When Harada flipped those two Dora indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.24,0:23:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,With his hidden Red Dragon Kan, it's a SanBaiMan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As the point value is so high, he can't deal into it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.52,0:23:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We survived
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.99,0:23:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If the kid were to deal into that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.99,0:23:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd only have 1000 points left
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.99,0:23:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much an act of suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.69,0:23:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus Ten's SanAnKou is no more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.59,0:23:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards Soga will collect a 4 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.22,0:23:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'll complete my hand and knock you out
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.72,0:23:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,no problem
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.90,0:24:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, kid. I took this hand last turn
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.78,0:24:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.22,0:24:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Ten won't even accept that direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.85,0:24:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the way it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that's your gut feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:24:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.72,0:24:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.55,0:25:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.12,0:25:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,24,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.80,0:25:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and SanAnKou has been cleared
